1.2.1 interactions

dat_sssst$int_cutest <- resid(
  lm(I(dat_sssst$group_di * dat_sssst$cu_total_mean) ~ dat_sssst$group_di + dat_sssst$cu_total_mean)
)
dat_sssst$int_cdtest <- resid(
  lm(I(dat_sssst$group_di * dat_sssst$sdq_cd) ~ dat_sssst$group_di + dat_sssst$sdq_cd)
)
dat_sssst$int_cucd <- resid(
  lm(I(dat_sssst$sdq_cd * dat_sssst$cu_total_mean) ~ dat_sssst$sdq_cd + dat_sssst$cu_total_mean)
)
dat_sssst$int_cucdtest <- resid(
  lm(
    I(dat_sssst$sdq_cd * dat_sssst$cu_total_mean * dat_sssst$group_di) ~ 
      dat_sssst$sdq_cd + dat_sssst$cu_total_mean + dat_sssst$group_di)
)

1.2.2 Recoding variables

1.2.2.1 Passive Control reaction time

1.2.2.1.1 Reverse coding & reasoning
  • For passive Control reaction time
    • longer times = better Control
    • shorter time = worse Control
  • This is the opposite of the selective Control and go trials
    • longer times = worse selective Control or go reaction
    • shorter times = better selective Control or go reaction
  • therefore - to have commensurate comparisons we reverse code by the following:
    • max rt (1.5) - rt (individual rt)
  • This results in a metric that is in the same direction as the others for interpretation as follows:
    • longer times = worse passive Control
    • shorter times = better passive Control
  • we will use this metric for analysis of passive Control trials
dat_sssst$ssst_mean_rt_ignore_rc <- (1.5-dat_sssst$ssst_mean_rt_ignore)
  • Additionally, we need to include the recording into the total reaction time
    • This better reflects the same direction of our reaction times
    • will be used in total reaction time analyses
dat_sssst$ssst_mean_rt_rc <- (
  (
    dat_sssst$ssst_mean_rt_go + 
      dat_sssst$ssst_mean_rt_ignore_rc + 
      dat_sssst$ssst_mean_rt_stop
    )/3
  )

4.1.1.2 Bootstrapped results

model <- m1
  ## extracting values
ssrt_coef <- coef(summary(model))
r2.adj_ssrt <- (1- ((1-summary(model)$r.squared)*(85-1)/(85-8-1)))

# bootstrapping
set.seed(46332)
aa<-simpleboot::lm.boot(model, R=1000, weights = runif(nrow(model.frame(model))))
ssrt_boot <- t(simpleboot::perc.lm(aa, p=c(0.025, 0.975)))

  ## adding bootstrapped ci to coefficients
ssrt_result <- cbind(ssrt_coef, ssrt_boot)

# Calculating bootstrap corrected p values
  # extracting bootstrapped values
p_v <- list()
ind <- 1
for(i in aa$boot.list){
  p_v[[ind]] <- ((as.data.frame(i$coef)[[1]]))
  ind <- ind+1
}
  # un-listing bootstrapped values for comparison 
vals <- as.numeric(unlist(p_v))
  # extracting model estimates
obs <- as.data.frame(coef(summary(model)))$Estimate

  # Organizing and scaling bootstrapped values for p value calculation
df <- list()
for(i in seq(1,length(vals), by= length(model$coefficients))){
  chunk <- (vals[i:(i+length(model$coefficients)-1)])
  chunk_df <- as.data.frame(t(chunk))
  df <- rbind(df,chunk_df)
}
  # calculating bootstrap corrected p values
p_value <- sapply(1:length(obs), function(i) {
  mean(abs(scale(df[, i], scale=FALSE)) >= abs(obs[i]))
})

p_values <- data.frame(boot_p = p_value)
  # binding boot p values
ssrt_result <- cbind(ssrt_result,p_values)

# calculating bootstrap corrected t values
t_value <- list()
for(ii in p_value){
  if(ii > 0){
    t_value <- append(t_value,qt(ii/2, 85-1, lower.tail = FALSE))
  } else{
    t_value <- append(t_value,qt(0.0001/2, 85-1, lower.tail = FALSE))
  }
}

for(ii in 1:length(t_value)){
  if(obs[ii] < 0)(
    t_value[[ii]] <- (-1)*t_value[[ii]]
  )
}

t_values <- data.frame(boot_t = unlist(t_value))

  # binding boot t values
ssrt_result <- cbind(ssrt_result,t_values)



  # binding r2
r2 <- t(as.data.frame((c(r2.adj_ssrt,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA, NA))))
rownames(r2) <- "Adj.R2"
colnames(r2) <- colnames(ssrt_result)
round(ssrt_result <- rbind(ssrt_result,r2), 3)
# saving results to csv
write.csv(
  ssrt_result,
  paste0(base,"\\ssrt_results.csv"),
  row.names=TRUE
  )

4.2.3.2 Bootstrapped results

model <- m5
  ## extracting values
rt_ignore_coef <- coef(summary(model))
r2.adj_rt_ignore <- (1-((1.5-summary(model)$adj.r.squared)*(85-1)/(85-12-1)))

# bootstrapping
set.seed(1979)
aa<-simpleboot::lm.boot(model, R=1000, weights = runif(nrow(model.frame(model))))
rt_ignore_boot <- t(simpleboot::perc.lm(aa, p=c(0.025, 0.975)))

  ## adding bootstrapped ci to coefficients
rt_ignore_result <- cbind(rt_ignore_coef, rt_ignore_boot)

# Calculating bootstrap corrected p values
  # extracting bootstrapped values
p_v <- list()
ind <- 1
for(i in aa$boot.list){
  p_v[[ind]] <- ((as.data.frame(i$coef)[[1]]))
  ind <- ind+1
}
  # un-listing bootstrapped values for comparison 
vals <- as.numeric(unlist(p_v))
  # extracting model estimates
obs <- as.data.frame(coef(summary(model)))$Estimate

  # Organizing and scaling bootstrapped values for p value calculation
df <- list()
for(i in seq(1,length(vals), by= length(model$coefficients))){
  chunk <- (vals[i:(i+length(model$coefficients)-1)])
  chunk_df <- as.data.frame(t(chunk))
  df <- rbind(df,chunk_df)
}
  # calculating bootstrap corrected p values
p_value <- sapply(1:length(obs), function(i) {
  mean(abs(scale(df[, i], scale=FALSE)) >= abs(obs[i]))
})

p_values <- data.frame(boot_p = p_value)
  # binding boot p values
rt_ignore_result <- cbind(rt_ignore_result,p_values)

# calculating bootstrap corrected t values
t_value <- list()
for(ii in p_value){
  if(ii > 0){
    t_value <- append(t_value,qt(ii/2, 85-1, lower.tail = FALSE))
  } else{
    t_value <- append(t_value,qt(0.0001/2, 85-1, lower.tail = FALSE))
  }
}

for(ii in 1:length(t_value)){
  if(obs[ii] < 0)(
    t_value[[ii]] <- (-1)*t_value[[ii]]
  )
}

t_values <- data.frame(boot_t = unlist(t_value))

  # binding boot t values
rt_ignore_result <- cbind(rt_ignore_result,t_values)



  # binding r2
r2 <- t(as.data.frame((c(r2.adj_rt_ignore,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA, NA))))
rownames(r2) <- "Adj.R2"
colnames(r2) <- colnames(rt_ignore_result)
round(rt_ignore_result <- rbind(rt_ignore_result,r2), 3)
# saving results to csv

  rt_ignore_result,
  paste0(base,"\\rt_ignore_results.csv"),
  row.names=TRUE

model <- m6
  ## extracting values
rt_stop_coef <- coef(summary(model))
r2.adj_rt_stop <- (1-((1.5-summary(model)$adj.r.squared)*(85-1)/(85-12-1)))

# bootstrapping
set.seed(1979)
aa<-simpleboot::lm.boot(model, R=1000, weights = runif(nrow(model.frame(model))))
rt_stop_boot <- t(simpleboot::perc.lm(aa, p=c(0.025, 0.975)))

  ## adding bootstrapped ci to coefficients
rt_stop_result <- cbind(rt_stop_coef, rt_stop_boot)

# Calculating bootstrap corrected p values
  # extracting bootstrapped values
p_v <- list()
ind <- 1
for(i in aa$boot.list){
  p_v[[ind]] <- ((as.data.frame(i$coef)[[1]]))
  ind <- ind+1
}
  # un-listing bootstrapped values for comparison

  # extracting model estimates

  )
}

t_values <- data.frame(boot_t = unlist(t_value))

  # binding boot t values
rt_stop_result <- cbind(rt_stop_result,t_values)




  # binding r2
r2 <- t(as.data.frame((c(r2.adj_rt_stop,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA, NA))))
rownames(r2) <- "Adj.R2"
colnames(r2) <- colnames(rt_stop_result)
round(rt_stop_result <- rbind(rt_stop_result,r2), 3)
# saving results to csv
write.csv(
  rt_stop_result,
  paste0(base,"\\rt_stop_results.csv"),
  row.names=TRUE
  )

model <- cct2
  ## extracting values
cont_acc_ignore_go_coef <- coef(summary(model))

# bootstrapping
set.seed(1979)
aa<-simpleboot::lm.boot(model, R=1000, weights = runif(nrow(model.frame(model))))
cont_acc_ignore_go_boot <- t(simpleboot::perc.lm(aa, p=c(0.025, 0.975)))

  ## adding bootstrapped ci to coefficients
cont_acc_ignore_go_result <- cbind(cont_acc_ignore_go_coef, cont_acc_ignore_go_boot)

# Calculating bootstrap corrected p values
  # extracting bootstrapped values
p_v <- list()
ind <- 1
for(i in aa$boot.list){
  p_v[[ind]] <- ((as.data.frame(i$coef)[[1]]))
  ind <- ind+1
}
  # un-listing bootstrapped values for comparison 
vals <- as.numeric(unlist(p_v))
  # extracting model estimates
obs <- as.data.frame(coef(summary(model)))$Estimate

  # Organizing and scaling bootstrapped values for p value calculation
df <- list()
for(i in seq(1,length(vals), by= length(model$coefficients))){
  chunk <- (vals[i:(i+length(model$coefficients)-1)])
  chunk_df <- as.data.frame(t(chunk))
  df <- rbind(df,chunk_df)
}
  # calculating bootstrap corrected p values
p_value <- sapply(1:length(obs), function(i) {
  mean(abs(scale(df[, i], scale=FALSE)) >= abs(obs[i]))
})

p_values <- data.frame(boot_p = p_value)
  # binding boot p values
cont_acc_ignore_go_result <- cbind(cont_acc_ignore_go_result,p_values)


# calculating bootstrap corrected t values
t_value <- list()
for(ii in p_value){
  if(ii > 0){
    t_value <- append(t_value,qt(ii/2, 85-1, lower.tail = FALSE))
  } else{
    t_value <- append(t_value,qt(0.0001/2, 85-1, lower.tail = FALSE))
  }
}

for(ii in 1:length(t_value)){
  if(obs[ii] < 0)(
    t_value[[ii]] <- (-1)*t_value[[ii]]
  )
}

t_values <- data.frame(boot_t = unlist(t_value))

  # binding boot t values
cont_acc_ignore_go_result <- cbind(cont_acc_ignore_go_result,t_values)

6.2 Balanced Integration Score (BIS)

  • Article: https://psycnet.apa.org/doi/10.3758/s13428-018-1076-x
  • Interpretation of this metric is
    • higher = better inhibitory control
    • lower = worse inhibitory control

6.2.1 calculating BIS

## Function
BIS <- function(rt_name, acc_name, output_name, data) {
  # Ensure rt_name, acc_name, and output_name are strings
  rt_name <- deparse(substitute(rt_name))
  acc_name <- deparse(substitute(acc_name))
  output_name <- deparse(substitute(output_name))
  
  # Find indices for the given column names
  rt_ind <- which(colnames(data) == rt_name)
  acc_ind <- which(colnames(data) == acc_name)
  
  # Ensure the specified column names exist in the dataset
  if (length(rt_ind) == 0 || length(acc_ind) == 0) {
    stop("One or more specified column names do not exist in the dataset.")
  }
  
  # Scale the selected columns
  z_rt <- scale(data[, rt_ind])
  z_acc <- scale(data[, acc_ind])
  
  # Compute the BIS
  BIS <- as.array(z_acc - z_rt)[1:NROW(data)]
  
  return(BIS)
}

## calculating with function 
dat_sssst$bis_overall <- BIS(ssst_mean_rt_rc, ssst_correct, overall, dat_sssst)
dat_sssst$bis_go <- BIS(ssst_mean_rt_go, ssst_correct_go, go, dat_sssst)
dat_sssst$bis_passive <- BIS(ssst_mean_rt_ignore_rc, ssst_correct_ignore, passive, dat_sssst)
dat_sssst$bis_selective <- BIS(ssst_mean_rt_stop, ssst_correct_stop, selective, dat_sssst)
